  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-a77e01e69a5b",
  "content": "# Generated by: corvia workspace init-hooks\n\n    });\n\n    if !already_exists {\n        arr.push(serde_json::json!({\n            \"matcher\": \"Write|Edit\",\n            \"hooks\": [{\"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"bash .corvia/hooks/doc-placement-check.sh\"}]\n        }));\n        let content = serde_json::to_string_pretty(&settings)\n            .map_err(|e| corvia_common::errors::CorviaError::Config(format!(\"Failed to serialize: {e}\")))?;\n        std::fs::write(&settings_path, content)\n            .map_err(|e| corvia_common::errors::CorviaError::Config(format!(\"Failed to write: {e}\")))?;\n        println!(\"  Updated: {}\", settings_path.display());\n    } else {\n        println!(\"  Skipped: {} (Write|Edit hook already registered)\", settings_path.display());\n    }\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Register module and wire command**\n\nIn `main.rs`, add `mod hooks;` and wire:\n\n```rust\nWorkspaceCommands::InitHooks => {\n    let root = std::env::current_dir()?;\n    let config = load_config()?;\n    hooks::generate_hooks(&root, &config)?;\n    Ok(())\n},\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Build and verify**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo build -p corvia-cli`\nExpected: Compiles. `corvia workspace init-hooks --help` shows the command.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-cli/src/hooks.rs crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(cli): add 'corvia workspace init-hooks' for hook generation from config\"\n```\n\n---\n",
